{{italictitle}}
The '''''Gesta Regum Anglorum''''' ([[Latin]] for "Deeds of the Kings of [[English people|the English]]"), originally titled {{nowrap|'''''De Gestis Regum Anglorum'''''}} ("On the Deeds of the Kings of the English") and also [[anglicization|anglicized]] as {{nowrap|'''''The Chronicles'''''}} or {{nowrap|'''''The History of the Kings of England'''''}}, is an early-12th-century [[history]] of the [[kings of England]] by [[William of Malmesbury]]. It is a companion work of his ''[[Gesta Pontificum Anglorum]]'' (''Deeds of the English Bishops'') and was followed by his ''Historia Novella'', which continued its account for several more years.

==Editions==
* {{citation |author=William of Malmesbury |display-authors=0 |title=The History of the Kings of England and the Modern History of William of Malmesbury |publisher=W. Bulmer & Co. for Longman, Hurst, Rees, Orme, & Brown |url=https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=wNZEAQAAMAAJ&pg=PR3  |editor-last=Sharpe |editor-first=John |location=London |date=1815 }}.
* {{citation |author=William of Malmesbury |display-authors=0 |contribution=Willelmi Malmesburiensis Monachi Gesta Regum Anglorum atque Historia Novella |pp=959–1390 |title=Saeculum XII: Willelmi Malmesburiensis Monachi Opera Omnia |volume=Vol.&nbsp;I |url=https://archive.org/stream/patrologiaecurs25unkngoog#page/n6/mode/2up |series=''[[Patrologiae Cursus Completus]]'', ''[[Patrologia Latina|Series Latina]]'', Vol.&nbsp;179 |contribution-url=https://archive.org/stream/patrologiaecurs25unkngoog#page/n480/mode/2up |editor-last=Hardy |editor-first=Thomas Duffus |location=Paris |date=1855 |editor2-last=Migne |editor2-first=Jacques-Paul |editor2-link=Jacques-Paul Migne |publisher=Paul Dupont for Garnier Bros. |display-editors=1 }}. {{la icon}}
* {{citation |author=William of Malmesbury |display-authors=0 |title=William of Malmesbury's Chronicle of the Kings of England: From the Earliest Period to the Reign of King Stephen, with Notes and Illustrations |editor-last=Giles |editor-first=J.A. |url=https://archive.org/stream/williamofmalmesb1847will#page/n5/mode/2up |location=London |publisher=Henry G. Bohn |date=1847 }}.
* {{citation |author=William of Malmesbury |display-authors=0 |title=Gesta Regum Anglorum |series=''Oxford Medieval Texts'' |location=Oxford |publisher=Clarendon Press |editor-last=Mynors |editor-first=R.A.B. |editor2-last=Thomson |editor2-first=R.M. |editor3-last=Winterbottom |editor3-first=Michael |display-editors=1 |date=1998 |volume=Vol.&nbsp;I |editor4-last=Greenway |editor4-first=D.E. |editor5-last=Harvey |editor5-first=B.F. |editor6-last=Lapidge |editor6-first=M. }}. {{la icon}}&nbsp;& {{en icon}}
