{{Infobox train | name= St. Louis Southwestern Railway (Cotton Belt Route) Steam Locomotive #336 | manufacturer = [[Baldwin Locomotive Works]] | yearconstruction = 1909 {{Infobox NRHP | embed = yes | name = St. Louis Southwestern Railway (Cotton Belt Route) Steam Locomotive #336 | nrhp_type = | image = St. Louis Southwestern Railway (Cotton Belt Route) Steam Locomotive 336.jpg | caption = | location = 1700 Port Rd., [[Arkansas Railroad Museum]], [[Pine Bluff, Arkansas]] | coordinates = {{coord|34|13|37|N|91|59|4|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Arkansas#USA | built = {{Start date|1909}} | added = January 24, 2007 | area = Less than one acre | governing_body = Private | refnum = 06001276<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} }}
The '''St. Louis Southwestern Railway (Cotton Belt Route) Steam Locomotive #336''' is a historic railroad steam locomotive, located at the [[Arkansas Railroad Museum]] in [[Pine Bluff, Arkansas]]. It is a Class D3 [[2-6-0]] Mogul-style locomotive, built in 1909 by the [[Baldwin Locomotive Works]] in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bailey|first1=Douglas C.|title=St. Louis Southwestern Ry No. 336|url=http://www.steamlocomotive.info/vlocomotive.cfm?Display=34|website=SteamLocomotive.info|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref> She served on the [[St. Louis Southwestern Railway]] (aka the Cotton Belt Route) until 1947, and served industrial customers until 1963. It was placed on display in [[Lewisville, Arkansas]] until 1994, when it was donated to the museum. It is the last remaining 330-series locomotive (of ten) used by the Cotton Belt.<ref name=NRHP>{{cite web|url=http://www.arkansaspreservation.com/National-Register-Listings/PDF/JE0575.nr.pdf|title=NRHP nomination for St. Louis Southwestern Railway (Cotton Belt Route) Steam Locomotive #336|accessdate=2015-12-13}}</ref>
The locomotive was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2007.<ref name="nris"/>
<gallery> File:St. Louis Southwestern Railway (Cotton Belt Route) Steam Locomotive 336, Historical Plaque.jpg|Plaque accompanying Steam Locomotive 336 </gallery>
